sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Customer<br/>(Informed)
    participant S as MKT Sales Team<br/>(Responsible)
    participant CO as Compliance Officer<br/>(Accountable)
    participant F as Finance<br/>(Responsible)
    participant FD as Finance Director<br/>(Accountable)
    participant IT as IT Ops<br/>(Consulted)

    C->>S: Submit onboarding request

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - Documentation Gate 1: Request Intake
    Note over S: 📋 DOC GATE 1:<br/>Log request in CRM,<br/>capture KYC documents,<br/>timestamp receipt
    S->>CO: Submit for initial compliance screening
    CO->>CO: SOX Control 1: Verify segregation of duties & requestor authorization
    CO-->>S: Compliance pre-clearance (or flag deficiencies)
    %% ⚡ END CHANGED SECTION

    S->>F: Credit check request

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - Risk assessment with SOX controls & documentation gates
    F->>F: Risk Assessment: Check credit score, company status, payment history

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - Documentation Gate 2: Risk Assessment Record
    Note over F: 📋 DOC GATE 2:<br/>Record risk score,<br/>assessment criteria,<br/>assessor identity & timestamp

    F->>CO: Submit risk assessment for SOX compliance review
    CO->>CO: SOX Control 2: Validate risk methodology, verify data sources, check for conflicts of interest
    CO-->>F: Compliance sign-off on risk assessment

    alt Low-Risk (Score >750 AND Verified Company AND Clean Payment History)
        F-->>S: Auto-Approved - Low Risk (Bypass Director)

        %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - SOX Control for auto-approval
        Note over F,CO: 📋 DOC GATE 3a:<br/>Log auto-approval rationale,<br/>attach compliance sign-off,<br/>retain audit trail
        F->>CO: Notify: auto-approval executed
        CO->>CO: SOX Control 3: Verify auto-approval within delegated authority limits
        CO-->>F: Auto-approval audit logged
        %% ⚡ END CHANGED SECTION

        S->>IT: Provision accounts (expedited)
        IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials (within 24h)
    else High-Risk (Score ≤750 OR Unverified OR Payment Issues)
        F->>FD: Escalate for Director approval

        %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - SOX Control for Director review
        Note over FD,CO: 📋 DOC GATE 3b:<br/>Director documents<br/>review rationale,<br/>risk acceptance/rejection basis
        FD->>CO: Submit decision for compliance validation
        CO->>CO: SOX Control 4: Verify Director authority level, check approval threshold compliance
        CO-->>FD: Compliance validated
        %% ⚡ END CHANGED SECTION

        FD-->>F: Director decision (24h SLA)
        alt Approved by Director
            F-->>S: Approval (Director reviewed)
            S->>IT: Provision accounts
            IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials
        else Rejected by Director
            F-->>S: Rejection with reasons

            %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - Documentation Gate for rejection
            Note over S: 📋 DOC GATE 4:<br/>Log rejection reasons,<br/>retain for dispute/audit
            %% ⚡ END CHANGED SECTION

            S->>C: Onboarding declined notification
        end
    end

    C->>IT: First login confirmation
    IT->>S: Onboarding complete

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - Final compliance checkpoint & documentation gate
    S->>CO: Submit completed onboarding for final compliance review
    CO->>CO: SOX Control 5: End-to-end audit trail review, verify all doc gates passed, confirm RACI adherence
    Note over CO: 📋 DOC GATE 5 (FINAL):<br/>Archive complete onboarding<br/>package: all approvals,<br/>risk assessments, compliance<br/>sign-offs, access grants
    CO-->>S: Final compliance certification issued
    Note over C,IT: RACI Summary:<br/>R=Sales,Finance | A=Compliance,FD<br/>C=IT | I=Customer
    %% ⚡ END CHANGED SECTION

    S->>C: Kickoff meeting scheduled

%% EXPLANATION:
%% Added a Compliance Officer (CO) participant labeled as Accountable in the RACI framework, and labeled all existing participants with their RACI roles (Responsible, Accountable, Consulted, Informed). Inserted five SOX control checkpoints: (1) segregation of duties verification at intake, (2) risk methodology validation after credit assessment, (3a/3b) authority-level verification for both auto-approvals and Director decisions, and (5) end-to-end audit trail review at completion. Added five corresponding documentation gates (marked with 📋) requiring formal logging of request intake, risk assessment records, approval/rejection rationale, and a final archived onboarding package. A RACI summary note was added at the end for quick reference.